cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NI 

This paper deals with information theory and communication channels, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of binary input channels, which could also place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The use of Bhattacharyya parameters may also suggest a connection to statistical inference and machine learning, which could place it in the cs.SI (Statistical Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on capacity and optimization could also suggest a connection to network information theory, which could place it in the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category.
